AttQuery(3)		Attitude File Functions		AttQuery(3)



NAME
     AttQuery - Attitude file query

SYNOPSIS
     #include "attlib.h"
	

     int AttQuery
               ( attEpoch  *att_time,
                 int       tocoord,
                 int       *attlevel,
                 double    matrix[DIM][DIM], /* DIM = 3 */
                 attAngles *angles
               );
     return values:  = 0     ERROR: DATA IS NOT FOUND
                     > 0     NO ERROR: DATA FOUND
                     < 0     FOUND THROUGH EXTRAPOLATION
 
     For successful return: attlevel_found = [abs(returnvalue)-1]
 
 
DESCRIPTION

     AttQuery() PARAMETERS:

        att_time: (input)
                Pointer to attEpoch contains date and time input.
                typedef struct {
                        int     year;     /* [1950-2049] */
                        int     doy;      /* [1-365] (1=Jan1)*/
                        int     hour;     /* [0-23] */
                        int     minute;   /* [0-59] */
                        double  seconds;  /* [0.-59.9] msecs */
                } attEpoch;

        tocoord: (input)
                Type of coordinate system wanted for the matrix.
                Options are below:
                        "Spinning Spacecraft[FASTSPIN]" FASTSPIN
                        "Despun[DESPUN]"                DESPUN
                        "Spacecraft[FASTMAG]"           FASTMAG
                        "Equatorial Inertial[GEI]"      GEI
                        "Geographic[GEO]"               GEO
                        "Solar Ecliptic[GSE]"           GSE
                        "Solar Magnetospheric[GSM]"     GSM
                        "Geomagnetic[MAG]"              MAG
                        "Ecliptic Inertial[GECI]"       GECI
                        "Solar Equatorial [GSEQ]"       GSEO
                        "Solar Magnetic [SM]"           SM

        attlevel: (input & output)
                Pointer to integer value. Set to the level of
                output the users would like. The range is 0-2.
                If the user just wants the best available output
                then the user can set attlevel to "BEST_ATT".

                On return, attlevel is set the level of data
                returned. If there is an error, then attlevel
                is set to BAD_ATT. 

        matrix: (output)
                Double of array of dimension DIM. Returns with
                the rotation matrix from FASTSPIN to the selected
                coordinate system.

        angles: (output)
                Pointer to attAngles which contains angle data.
                Spin right ascension & declination in GEI coords.
                typedef struct {
                        double spin_ra;
                        double spin_dec;
                        double spin_phase;
                        double spin_freq;
                } attAngles;

